{"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"SwiftCrossUI"}],"title":"GtkBackend","roleHeading":"Article","role":"article"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"While Gtk isn’t the preferred UI framework on every Linux distro, it’s the closest thing SwiftCrossUI has to a native Linux backend for now. The Qt backend may be brought back to life at some point to cover the rest of Linux distros.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For targetting older pre Gtk 4 Linux distros, see the secondary "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/Gtk3Backend","type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This backend supports Linux, macOS, and Windows, but its support for macOS has a few known issues worse due to underlying Gtk issues (and its support for Windows isn’t well tested).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"System dependencies","anchor":"System-dependencies","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Before you can use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkBackend"},{"type":"text","text":" you must install the required system dependencies for your platform. Here are installation instructions tailored to each supported platform;"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"text":"Linux","anchor":"Linux","type":"heading"},{"code":["# Debian-based distros","sudo apt install libgtk-4-dev clang","","# Fedora-based distros","sudo dnf install gtk4-devel clang"],"syntax":"sh","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figure 1: "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"installing the required dependencies on Debian-based and Fedora-based Linux distros"}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you run into errors related to not finding "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gtk\/gtk.h"},{"type":"text","text":" when trying to build a swift-cross-ui project, try restarting your computer. This has worked in some cases (although there may be a more elegant solution)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you are on a non-Debian non-Fedora distro and the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkBackend"},{"type":"text","text":" requirements end up differing significantly from the requirements stated above, please open a GitHub issue or PR so that we can improve the documentation."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"macOS","anchor":"macOS"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"sh","code":["brew install pkg-config gtk4"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Figure 2: ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"installing the required dependencies using Homebrew"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you don’t have Homebrew, installation instructions can be found at ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/brew.sh","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It should also be possible to use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gtk4"},{"type":"text","text":" installed via MacPorts, but I have not tested that."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you run into errors related to ","type":"text"},{"code":"libffi","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"code":"FFI","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" when trying to build a swift-cross-ui project with ","type":"text"},{"code":"GtkBackend","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", which can occur when certain older versions of the Xcode Command Line Tools are installed, try running the following command to patch libffi:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"sh","code":["sed -i '' 's\/-I..includedir.\/\/g' $(brew --prefix)\/Library\/Homebrew\/os\/mac\/pkgconfig\/*\/libffi.pc"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Figure 3: ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"fixing the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"libffi"},{"type":"text","text":" issue that some people face"}],"type":"emphasis"}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Windows","anchor":"Windows"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"On Windows things are a bit complicated (as usual), so we only support installation via ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/microsoft\/vcpkg"},{"text":". First, install vcpkg;","type":"text"}]},{"code":["git clone https:\/\/github.com\/microsoft\/vcpkg C:\\vcpkg","C:\\vcpkg\\bootstrap-vcpkg.bat"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"sh"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Figure 4: ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"install vcpkg (requires git cli)"}],"type":"emphasis"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It’s important to install vcpkg at the root of a drive due to limitations of the Gtk build system."}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Warning","style":"warning"},{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"After installation, make the following changes to your environment variables:","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Set the ","type":"text"},{"code":"PKG_CONFIG_PATH","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" environment variable to ","type":"text"},{"code":"C:\\vcpkg\\installed\\x64-windows\\lib\\pkgconfig","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". This is only required for building.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"C:\\vcpkg\\installed\\x64-windows\\bin"},{"type":"text","text":" to your "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Path"},{"type":"text","text":" environment variable. This is only required for running."}]}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"With vcpkg installed, you have two options for Gtk installation; global installation, and project-local installation"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":4,"text":"Global Gtk 4 installation (recommended)","anchor":"Global-Gtk-4-installation-recommended","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Note that the command depends on your machine’s architecture; choose between Figure 5 and Figure 6 accordingly.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Installation can take 45+ minutes depending on your machine."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["C:\\vcpkg\\vcpkg.exe install gtk --triplet x64-windows"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"sh"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Figure 5: ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"install Gtk 4 globally on x64 Windows","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["C:\\vcpkg\\vcpkg.exe install gtk --triplet arm64-windows"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"sh"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figure 6: "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"install Gtk 4 globally on arm64 Windows"}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Run the chosen command at the root of your drive to ensure that vcpkg doesn’t run in manifest mode."}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Warning","style":"warning"},{"level":4,"text":"Project-local Gtk 4 installation (more unreliable)","anchor":"Project-local-Gtk-4-installation-more-unreliable","type":"heading"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If the absolute path to your project contains spaces, it is possible that vcpkg will break, and installing globally will be a more reliable strategy.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","name":"Note","style":"note"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To install Gtk 4 in a project-local dependency store you must setup a ","type":"text"},{"code":"vcpkg.json","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" manifest file and then run vcpkg, as detailed below;","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"First "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"vcpkg.json"},{"type":"text","text":" at the root of your project and make sure that it includes the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gtk"},{"type":"text","text":" dependency as demonstrated in Figure 7."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["{","    \"name\": \"project-name\",","    \"version-string\": \"main\",","    \"dependencies\": [\"gtk\"]","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"json"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Figure 7: ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"an example "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"vcpkg.json"},{"type":"text","text":" package manifest"}],"type":"emphasis"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["C:\\vcpkg\\vcpkg.exe install --triplet x64-windows"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"sh"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Figure 8: ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"install the dependencies listed in your package manifest"}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Replace the triplet with ","type":"text"},{"code":"arm64-windows","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" if you’re on ARM64","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","name":"Warning","style":"warning"},{"level":2,"text":"Usage","anchor":"Usage","type":"heading"},{"code":["...","","let package = Package(","  ...","  targets: [","    ...","    .executableTarget(","      name: \"YourApp\",","      dependencies: [","        .product(name: \"SwiftCrossUI\", package: \"swift-cross-ui\"),","        .product(name: \"GtkBackend\", package: \"swift-cross-ui\"),","      ]","    )","    ...","  ]","  ...",")"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Figure 9: ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"adding ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkBackend"},{"text":" to an executable target","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["import SwiftCrossUI","import GtkBackend","","@main","struct YourApp: App {","  \/\/ You can explicitly initialize your app's chosen backend if you desire.","  \/\/ This happens automatically when you import any of the built-in backends.","  \/\/","  \/\/ var backend = GtkBackend()","  \/\/","  \/\/ If you aren't using Swift Bundler, you may have to explicitly provide","  \/\/ your app's identifier for some GtkBackend features to work correctly","  \/\/ (such as handling custom URL schemes).","  \/\/","  \/\/ var backend = GtkBackend(appIdentifier: \"com.example.YourApp\")","","  var body: some Scene {","    WindowGroup {","      Text(\"Hello, World!\")","        .padding()","    }","  }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Figure 10: ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkBackend"}],"type":"emphasis"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI","doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/Built-in-backends"]]},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"SwiftCrossUI’s native Linux backend built on top of Gtk 4.","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/GtkBackend","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/DefaultBackend","doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/AppKitBackend","doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/UIKitBackend","doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/WinUIBackend","doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/Gtk3Backend"],"generated":true}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftcrossui\/gtkbackend"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"references":{"https://brew.sh":{"titleInlineContent":[{"text":"brew.sh","type":"text"}],"url":"https:\/\/brew.sh","title":"brew.sh","type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/brew.sh"},"doc://SwiftCrossUI/document